# This is NOT the Next.js you know

This version has breaking changes — APIs, conventions, and file structure may all differ from your training data. Read the relevant guide in `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before writing any code. Heed deprecation notices.

## Scene preview routes (dev)

Use fixed-scene preview pages to test sky, weather FX, and garden panning without live APIs.

```bash
npm run dev:web
```

Index: [http://localhost:3000/preview](http://localhost:3000/preview)

| Route | Scene |
|-------|--------|
| `/preview/dawn` | Dawn, partly cloudy |
| `/preview/day` | Midday, clear |
| `/preview/golden-hour` | Golden hour |
| `/preview/heavy-rain` | Heavy rain + demo lightning |

- Presets: `apps/web/lib/scene/preview-scenes.ts`
- Renderer: `apps/web/components/scene/WeatherPreviewScene.tsx`
- Pages: `apps/web/app/preview/<slug>/page.tsx`

When adding a preview: export scene + add to `PREVIEW_ROUTES`, create a page with `WeatherPreviewScene`.
